reviewText: I am very satisfied and happy with my box set of Vegas' 1st Season.  It arrived on time and for a very good price.  The double pack was even cheaper than the 2 parts sold separately.  I would recommend this to anyone who was a fan of Vegas.

reviewText: This series  Vegas - with Robert Urich is a great fast moving private detective in Las Vegas  who always solves his assignments.  There some humor,  some sadness, some romance which makes it a great show. Robert Urich plays Dan Tanna who is absolutely gorgeous and he plays the part very well.  I watch this series over and over again  and I would not hestitate to recommend it to  anyone.  Very enjoyable!!!!

reviewText: Ok this review is not for the show but how it is released.  I loved the show when it was on TV and I have waited patiently for it to come out on DVD, but this piece meal BS is just too much. Just release the whole thing at once and be done with it. It is not like you have to wait for them to complete the episodes or something. *headdesk*
summary: Love the show but why not just release all of it at once

reviewText: Robert Urich was a talented actor (even if they made him wear those ridiculously-tight jeans).  This show not only had good writing, it also captured the flash & exitement of Las Vegas.  I also like the humorous characters who guest-starred in several episodes.  Besides....who wouldn't want to park their vintage T-Bird convertible inside their house & just hop out without opening the door?  The outfits of that period will make you smile.
